3. Responsibilities
-------------------

3.1. Distribution of Source Form

All distribution of Covered Software in Source Code form, including any
Modifications that You create or to which You contribute, must be under
the terms of this License. You must inform recipients that the Source
Code form of Covered Software is governed by the terms of this License,
and how they can obtain a copy of this License. You may not attempt to
alter or restrict the recipients' rights in the Source Code form.

3.2. Distribution of Executable Form

If You distribute Covered Software in Executable form then:

(a) such Covered Software must also be made available in Source Code
    form, as described in Section 3.1, and You must inform recipients of
    the Executable form how they can obtain a copy of such Source Code
    form by reasonable means in a timely manner, at a charge no more
    than the cost of distribution to the recipient; and

(b) You may distribute such Executable form under the terms of this
    License, or sublicense it under different terms, provided that the
    license for the Executable form does not attempt to limit or alter
    the recipients' rights in the Source Code form under this License.

3.3. Distribution of a Larger Work

You may create and distribute a Larger Work under terms of Your choice,
provided that You also comply with the requirements of this License for
the Covered Software. If the Larger Work is a combination of Covered
Software with a work governed by one or more Secondary Licenses, and the
Covered Software is not Incompatible With Secondary Licenses, this
License permits You to additionally distribute Covered Software under
the terms of such Secondary License(s), so that the use of the Covered
Software is not restricted by this License.

3.4. Notices

When You distribute Covered Software, You must keep intact all copyright,
patent, trademark, and attribution notices that are contained in the
Covered Software, except that You do not need to retain any notices that
do not pertain to any part of the Covered Software You are distributing.

If the Covered Software has a "NOTICE" text file as part of its
distribution, then any Covered Software You distribute must include a
readable copy of the attribution notices contained within such NOTICE
file, excluding those notices that do not pertain to any part of the
Covered Software You are distributing, unless those notices are provided
in a manner sufficient for the recipient to understand that such notices
do not apply to the Covered Software You are distributing.

3.5. Applications

You may apply the Mozilla Public License to files which are not already
subject to the Mozilla Public License. However, if You do so, You must
also comply with the requirements of Section 3.4.

